Reasoning: The paper deals with coding theory and its application to information storage systems, specifically DNA storage systems. It discusses the construction and bounds of codes that correct fixed length duplication errors, which falls under the category of error-correcting codes. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). Other likely sub-categories include cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
